---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../config";
---

<BaseLayout title={`${SITE_TITLE} - Aboute`}>
    <div class="mb-5 content-center text-center text-xl">
        <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-4">Aboute</div>
        <div class="mb-12 text-base">
            Here is the text I wrote for the last version of this page and
            didn't have time to replace it.
        </div>
        <div class="mb-10">
            I live in Krakow and I am student. My favorite color is blue which
            you can see from the appearance of this page.
        </div>
        <div class="mb-10">
            I am also a programmer. I wrote in many languages. Currently my main
            language is <strong>Python</strong>
            but I wrote a lot in <strong>C++</strong>, <strong>PHP</strong>, <strong
                >C#</strong
            > and I recently learned basics of
            <strong>Java</strong>. I also wrote mobile applications with <strong
                >Flutter</strong
            > and android games in <strong>Unity</strong> engine (You can download
            some of them <a
                class="link-primary"
                href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/developer?id=Stairs+Adventure+Studio"
                target="_blanck">here</a
            >).
        </div>
        <div class="mb-10">
            I write webpages mainly using the <strong>React</strong>. On backend
            I used
            <strong>Django</strong>, <strong>Express.js</strong> or even <strong
                >Strapi</strong
            > and <strong>FastAPI</strong>. I have some expirers in using
            <strong>Three.js</strong>. I'm also interested in electronics, more
            specifically IoT and home automation.
        </div>
        <div class="mb-10">
            In free time I like go hiking in the mountains, fold origami and
            ride a bicycle. Also, I know how to arrange Rubik's cube and
            recently I am learning to play the guitar.
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
